<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-617-725  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 617 725.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Networking Management  Nov 1990 v8 n11 p93(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Students stay connected with fiber-optic network. (Harvey MuddCollege)andM;</TITLE><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Students at Harvey Mudd College have free and unlimited time on anetwork of more than 40 computers and can access a supercomputer.andO;The college's fiber-optic backbone network is connected in a10M-bps Ethernet configuration that includes the other fivecolleges in the Claremont Colleges system and the main library.andO;The network has over 10,000 meters of AMP fiber-optic cable,approximately 200 pairs of AMP ST-type fiber-optic connectors andcoupling receptacles, and a number of passive optical couplers.andP;  Abayonet configuration is used for quick connect/disconnect forinstallation, modification, and testing.andP;  There are three hubs onthe backbone optical network: two at Harvey Mudd and one that iscentral to the other colleges.andP;  There are two gateways to provideaccess to other research and academic networks, permittingstudents to use computing services outside the Claremont complex.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Colleges and UniversitiesNetworksFiber OpticsEthernetHarvey Mudd CollegeClaremont Colleges.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>